      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Why are venture capitalists investing heavily in climate tech?</summary>
        <p>Venture capitalists see climate tech as a massive generational opportunity, driven by increasing regulatory pressures, shifting consumer demands, and the urgent global necessity to decarbonize the economy.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How does investing in climate tech differ from traditional software VC?</summary>
        <p>Climate tech often involves 'hard tech' or physical infrastructure, which requires more upfront capital, longer development timelines, and carries distinct regulatory and execution risks compared to traditional SaaS (Software as a Service) investments.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the expected ROI for climate tech investments?</summary>
